column5: This is from last Friday where we spent the morning on the water. We ended up going 6/10 between three of us with the biggest fish being 44". Also had a few bloopers with a rod slipping out of my hand during a hookset and one of us not using a proper musky leader and paying the price for it. Overall a very fun morning. Also lost a 50" class fish!
Sweet video. The success and heartbreak of musky fishing, got to love it! Great stuff!
I'd fire the net man on the one that swam out of the basket doh
nice video. funny fail with the rod slip. Net man needs to be fired for that musky swimming out.
Nice guys!!! Droping the rod was a classic for the blooper reel.
Excellent video. I was there in August for the 1st time. We boated 2 using bondy baits.   Congrats!
Thanks! The jigging bite is so much fun.

Thanks guys. Here's the link to my latest video in case anyone interested. Im trying to post a new one every Wednesday at 6pm. Going to be a struggle with the winds in the next 7 days around here though!
Nice work!!  We were thinking about going today, but heard weather has been bad. Going to try for monday.....
I went shore casting this morning and didn't get a bite, crazy windy out there.
Glad i didn't do the 2.5hr trip then....  thanks for the updates!!
